{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778988238918,"sessionID":"ses_1cc17a755ffeHlmzTMQRuy0Np3","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_Tzl21n1wllqiJGaJ6UpksQur","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n+Added a new `p24 cargo receptor complex` term as a child of `cargo receptor complex` for issue #31295.\n+\n+The term is intended for the conserved p24 hetero-oligomeric cargo receptor complex involved in selective ER export in the early secretory pathway.\n+\n+Changes committed locally and ready for PR #<NN>.\n*** Add File: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/PR_COMMENTS.md\n+Added a new GO cellular component term:\n+\n+- `GO:7770070` `p24 cargo receptor complex`\n+\n+Rationale:\n+\n+- The issue requested a term for the conserved p24 complex, which cannot be adequately captured by the generic parent `GO:0062137 cargo receptor complex`.\n+- Literature supports treating the p24 complex as a bona fide cargo receptor complex in the early secretory pathway, particularly for selective ER export in COPII-mediated anterograde trafficking.\n+- The complex is conserved and hetero-oligomeric, typically containing members of the p24 alpha, beta, gamma, and delta subfamilies.\n+\n+Modeling decisions:\n+\n+- Parent: `GO:0062137 cargo receptor complex`\n+- Relationship: `capable_of_part_of GO:0006888 ! endoplasmic reticulum to Golgi vesicle-mediated transport`\n+- I did not add `intersection_of` axioms because this is a named biological complex and there is no suitable documented compositional design pattern that would justify necessary-and-sufficient conditions here.\n+- I also did not assert a location such as `part_of endoplasmic reticulum exit site`; the ER-exit-site localization is biologically relevant, but the core identity of the term is the cargo receptor complex itself and its role in anterograde secretory trafficking.\n+\n+Validation and research performed:\n+\n+- Read the full imported issue context and comments.\n+- Consulted existing ontology precedent, especially:\n+  - `GO:0062137 cargo receptor complex`\n+  - `GO:0061852 retrograde cargo receptor complex, Golgi to ER`\n+- Created temporary `DESIGN_PATTERNS.md` and `RESEARCH.md` notes.\n+- Validated supporting literature excerpts in `RESEARCH.md` with:\n+  - `linkml-reference-validator validate text-file -r 'SUPPORT: (\\S+:\\S+) \"(.*)\"' -t 2 -R 1 RESEARCH.md`\n+- Ran pre-edit validation: `make travis_build`\n+- Added the new term through the small-file checkin workflow:\n+  - created `terms/GO_7770070.obo`\n+  - checked in with `obo-checkin.pl src/ontology/go-edit.obo terms/GO_7770070.obo`\n+- Ran post-edit validation: `make travis_build`\n+\n+Checklist:\n+\n+- [x] PLAN: issue context analyzed and intent clear\n+- [x] PRE-VALIDATION: ontology validated before edits\n+- [x] RESEARCH: literature checked and `RESEARCH.md` created\n+- [x] TERM-SEARCH: existing GO terms and precedent reviewed\n+- [x] DESIGN-PATTERNS: pattern assessment documented in `DESIGN_PATTERNS.md`\n+- [x] EDITS: used top-level `terms/` plus `obo-checkin.pl`\n+- [x] RELATIONSHIPS: parent and process relationship added; no overspecified axioms\n+- [x] METADATA: new term includes `created_by`, `creation_date`, and `term_tracker_item`\n+- [x] AUTOMATED-VALIDATION: `make travis_build` passed after changes\n+- [x] REFERENCE-VALIDATION: references validated against PubMed content\n+- [x] CHANGES-COMMITTED: ontology edit committed locally\n+\n+Commit:\n+\n+- `5173325` `Add p24 cargo receptor complex`\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\nA PR_COMMENTS.md","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,5 @@\n+Added a new `p24 cargo receptor complex` term as a child of `cargo receptor complex` for issue #31295.\n+\n+The term is intended for the conserved p24 hetero-oligomeric cargo receptor complex involved in selective ER export in the early secretory pathway.\n+\n+Changes committed locally and ready for PR #<NN>.\n\nIndex: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/PR_COMMENTS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/PR_COMMENTS.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/PR_COMMENTS.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,49 @@\n+Added a new GO cellular component term:\n+\n+- `GO:7770070` `p24 cargo receptor complex`\n+\n+Rationale:\n+\n+- The issue requested a term for the conserved p24 complex, which cannot be adequately captured by the generic parent `GO:0062137 cargo receptor complex`.\n+- Literature supports treating the p24 complex as a bona fide cargo receptor complex in the early secretory pathway, particularly for selective ER export in COPII-mediated anterograde trafficking.\n+- The complex is conserved and hetero-oligomeric, typically containing members of the p24 alpha, beta, gamma, and delta subfamilies.\n+\n+Modeling decisions:\n+\n+- Parent: `GO:0062137 cargo receptor complex`\n+- Relationship: `capable_of_part_of GO:0006888 ! endoplasmic reticulum to Golgi vesicle-mediated transport`\n+- I did not add `intersection_of` axioms because this is a named biological complex and there is no suitable documented compositional design pattern that would justify necessary-and-sufficient conditions here.\n+- I also did not assert a location such as `part_of endoplasmic reticulum exit site`; the ER-exit-site localization is biologically relevant, but the core identity of the term is the cargo receptor complex itself and its role in anterograde secretory trafficking.\n+\n+Validation and research performed:\n+\n+- Read the full imported issue context and comments.\n+- Consulted existing ontology precedent, especially:\n+  - `GO:0062137 cargo receptor complex`\n+  - `GO:0061852 retrograde cargo receptor complex, Golgi to ER`\n+- Created temporary `DESIGN_PATTERNS.md` and `RESEARCH.md` notes.\n+- Validated supporting literature excerpts in `RESEARCH.md` with:\n+  - `linkml-reference-validator validate text-file -r 'SUPPORT: (\\S+:\\S+) \"(.*)\"' -t 2 -R 1 RESEARCH.md`\n+- Ran pre-edit validation: `make travis_build`\n+- Added the new term through the small-file checkin workflow:\n+  - created `terms/GO_7770070.obo`\n+  - checked in with `obo-checkin.pl src/ontology/go-edit.obo terms/GO_7770070.obo`\n+- Ran post-edit validation: `make travis_build`\n+\n+Checklist:\n+\n+- [x] PLAN: issue context analyzed and intent clear\n+- [x] PRE-VALIDATION: ontology validated before edits\n+- [x] RESEARCH: literature checked and `RESEARCH.md` created\n+- [x] TERM-SEARCH: existing GO terms and precedent reviewed\n+- [x] DESIGN-PATTERNS: pattern assessment documented in `DESIGN_PATTERNS.md`\n+- [x] EDITS: used top-level `terms/` plus `obo-checkin.pl`\n+- [x] RELATIONSHIPS: parent and process relationship added; no overspecified axioms\n+- [x] METADATA: new term includes `created_by`, `creation_date`, and `term_tracker_item`\n+- [x] AUTOMATED-VALIDATION: `make travis_build` passed after changes\n+- [x] REFERENCE-VALIDATION: references validated against PubMed content\n+- [x] CHANGES-COMMITTED: ontology edit committed locally\n+\n+Commit:\n+\n+- `5173325` `Add p24 cargo receptor complex`\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md","relativePath":"ISSUE_COMMENTS.md","type":"add","patch":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,5 @@\n+Added a new `p24 cargo receptor complex` term as a child of `cargo receptor complex` for 